info.name: Cisco IOS-XE RESTCONF
info.description: Collection of RESTCONF requests related to the DEVASc, DEVCOR, and ENAUTO exams.

item.name: Authentication Examples
item.description: Various response examples based on successful and failed requests.

item.name: OpenConfig Switchports

response.name: Success: all interfaces (cat9k)
Success: gig1/0/17 after config (cat9k)
Success: gig1/0/17 before config (cat9k)

item.description: Manages layer-2 switchports using OpenConfig YANG models. In the course, I demonstrated this using NETCONF to NX-OS, so these requests have been adapted to work in a RESTCONF environment.

item.name: IETF Static Routes
item.description: Managing static routes using the IETF YANG models.

item.name: IETF Interfaces

response.name: Success: before addition
Success: after addition

item.description: Manage interfaces using the IETF YANG models.

item.name: Cisco Native DHCP Pools
item.description: Manage DHCP pools using the Cisco Native YANG models.

item.name: Cisco Native VLANs

response.name: Failure: bad request (csr1k)

item.description: Manage VLANs using the Cisco Native YANG models. These API calls only apply to switches.

item.name: Cisco Native Telemetry Subscriptions
item.description: Manage gRPC dial-out telemetry subscriptions using Cisco Native YANG models. This requires IOS-XE 16.12 or later.
